    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-11T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-11T04:00:00-05:00" n="349"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d349">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/4–1149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Edgar</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Taipei</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-11T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 11, 1949—5 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 11—8:57 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>111. From Merchant. Deptel 607, April 7 not seen by me prior despatch my telegram
                    1130 of April 9 or my letter to Butterworth of April 8.<note n="29"
                        xml:id="d349fn29">Letter not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Regarding appraisal requested Deptel under reference will be sent soonest.</p>
                <p>Reference Taipei’s 108, April 10 and 110, April 11, I plan lie low and not now
                    plan to see T. V. in absence contrary guidance. [Merchant.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edgar</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
